asha stanford's holi 2010 asha stanford's holi 2010 among india's innumerable festivals holi ranks as the most colorful it heralds the arrival of spring with the promise of good harvests and fertility asha for education is celebrating holi at stanford on a grand scale with expected attendance of 4500 based on past years we invite you to join us in spraying each other with color and water and in dancing to our dj's rocking tunes net proceeds from this event go towards supporting educational movements for the underprivileged in india more information date and time saturday march 27 2010 11 00 am approximate duration of 4 hour s location sandhill fields stanford university map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members category social events dance arts sponsor asha for education stanford chapter contact 650 644 7178 nikit stanford edu admission general $14 by march 20 $16 thereafter student with valid id $12 by march 20 $14 thereafter free admission for kids 5 and under 10 discount available for groups of 25 or more stanford holi ashanet org download add to personal calendar vcal record email event print use this permalink last modified march 17 2010
